                </accordion-wc>
                <footer data-layout="cluster" data-layout-gap="s">
                  <button type="button">Save Changes</button>
                  <button type="button" class="secondary" popovertarget="confirm-reset-compare-js">Reset</button>
                </footer>
                <div id="confirm-reset-compare-js" popover>
                  <p>Reset all settings to defaults?</p>
                  <footer data-layout="cluster" data-layout-gap="s">
                    <button type="button" popovertarget="confirm-reset-compare-js">Cancel</button>
                    <button type="button" class="ghost">Confirm</button>
                  </footer>
                </div>
              </section>
            </output>
          </browser-window>
          <figcaption class="pe-caption">One script adds keyboard navigation (<kbd>&uarr;</kbd><kbd>&darr;</kbd> <kbd>Home</kbd> <kbd>End</kbd>), ARIA roles, command palette, and 30 interactive components.</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </details>
    </tab-set>

    <p class="pe-meta"><small>This section is itself a progressive enhancement demo — without JavaScript, <code>&lt;tab-set&gt;</code> degrades to a native exclusive accordion via the <code>name</code> attribute on <code>&lt;details&gt;</code>.</small></p>
  </section>

  <!-- Features Section -->
  <section class="features-section">
    <h2 data-reveal>Built Different</h2>
    <ul data-layout="grid" data-layout-min="280px" data-layout-gap="l">
      <li>
        <article class="card">
          <h3>
            <icon-wc name="file-code" size="sm"></icon-wc>
            HTML-First
          </h3>
          <p>114 native elements styled out of the box. <code>&lt;details&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;dialog&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;kbd&gt;</code>, <code>[popover]</code> — real HTML, not <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> abstractions.</p>
        </article>
      </li>
      <li>
        <article class="card">
          <h3>
            <icon-wc name="layers" size="sm"></icon-wc>
            Progressive Enhancement
          </h3>
